{[#] Black is very active and thought this was a good moment to exchange in
the centre with} 12... Nxd4 {White did not like the prospect of defending a
slightly worse symmetrical position after 13.cxd4 Qd6 and went for the
principled} 13. Nxd4 {Was this a good decision? ***No, it was not!} Rxe2 $1 {
wins more or less by force.} 14. Nxe2 ({The intermediate} 14. f3 {does not
work:} Qe7 15. fxg4 Qe4 16. Rf2 Re1+) 14... Qe7 15. Re1 ({A better practical
chance would have been} 15. Be3 Bxe3 16. fxe3 Qxe3+ 17. Rf2 Ne4 18. Qd4 Qxf2+
19. Qxf2 Nxf2 20. Kxf2 Bxe2 21. Kxe2 f6 $17 {even though Black has every
reason to count on winning.}) 15... Re8 16. Kf1 ({I was slightly worried by} 
16. Bg5 Bxe2 17. Qd2 {but it appears that after} Qe4 18. Bxf6 (18. Rac1 Ng4 $19
) (18. h3 Re5 $19) 18... gxf6 {White is not in time to use the pin along the
e-file while Black can start an attack along the g-file.} 19. Rac1 Kh8 20. Rc2
(20. Qh6 Rg8 21. Qxf6+ Rg7 22. g3 Kg8 {followed by ...Rg6-+.}) 20... Rg8 21. g3
Bxf2+ $1 22. Kxf2 Qf3+ 23. Kg1 Rxg3+ 24. hxg3 Qxg3+ 25. Kh1 Bf3+ 26. Qg2 Qxe1+
{wins.}) 16... Ne4 17. Be3 Bxe3 18. fxe3 Qf6+ 19. Kg1 Qf2+ 20. Kh1 Qxe3 21. Qd4
Nf2+ 22. Kg1 Nd3+ 23. Qxe3 Rxe3 24. Red1 Bxe2 25. Rd2 h5 26. a4 Bg4 27. a5 a6
28. Kf1 h4 0-1

