{[#]White tried questioning Black's stability in the centre with} 16. Ng5 {
when Black correctly answered with} Nxd4 {, the only move avoiding trouble.
How should White deal with the tensioned situation?} 17. Qxd4 $2 {This loses
material.} (17. cxd4 Rc2 $17 {would also be unsatisfactory after the forced}
18. Qe1) ({The only move to keep White in the game was} 17. Bg4 $3 Bxg2 $5 ({
The most interesting continuation.} 17... Nc6 $2 {leaves Black hanging:} 18.
Nxe4 dxe4 19. Bxc8 $18) (17... f5 {leads to simplifications and a probable
draw:} 18. Nxe4 dxe4 19. Qxd4 fxg4 20. Qxd6 $11) 18. Kxg2 Nf5 19. Qxd5 (19.
Bxf5 Nh4+ {retrieves the knight with an advantage.}) 19... Rc5 20. Qxc5 $1 (20.
Qd2 Nxe3+ {followed by ...Rxg5 is bad the same as}) (20. Bxc5 Nf4+) 20... Bxc5
21. Rxd8 Nxe3+ 22. fxe3 Rxd8 23. Nxf7 Rd2+ {with interesting play and even
chances.}) 17... Bc5 18. Qd2 Bxe3 19. Qxe3 Bxg2 $1 $17 {A small trick winning
at least a pawn.} 20. Kxg2 $2 Re8 21. Nxf7 (21. Qd2 Rxe2 $19) 21... Rxe3 22.
Nxd8 Nf4+ 23. Kg1 Rxe2 $19 0-1

