{[#]Black is very active but the voluntary retreat} 16. Ne2 $2 {made things
worse. Why?} Bxh3 $1 {With the g1-a7 diagonal available to the other bishop
this sacrifice wins.} 17. Bf4 (17. gxh3 Rxe2 $1 (17... Bxf2+ {is also strong
since} 18. Kxf2 Qh2+ 19. Kf1 Re3 {or 19.Kf3 Re3!+ 20.Bxe3 Ne5#.}) 18. Rxe2 (18.
Bxe2 {does not change much:} Qg3+ 19. Kh1 Qxh3+ 20. Kg1 Bxf2+ 21. Kxf2 Ne4+ 22.
Kg1 Qg3+ 23. Kh1 Nf2#) 18... Qg3+ 19. Kh1 Qxh3+ 20. Kg1 Ng4 21. Bf4 g5 $1 $19)
17... Qd7 $17 ({This is strong enough but the spectacular} 17... Rxe2 $3 {
is even more convincing:} 18. Bxc7 Bxf2+ 19. Kh2 Rxe1 {Now or on the next move
White has to return the queen, as} 20. Qc2 Ne3 21. Qd2 {allows} Bxg2 {[%cal
Gf6g4] threatening ...Nfg4#.}) 18. gxh3 (18. Bxc4 dxc4 19. gxh3 Qxh3 20. Nbd4
Re4 {also offers a decisive attack.}) 18... Qxh3 {(/\...Nxb2)} 19. Bxc4 Qg4+
20. Kf1 (20. Bg3 Rxe2 $1) 20... Bxf2 (20... Qf3 $1 {is even stronger:} 21. Nbd4
Bxd4 22. Qxd4 Rxe2 23. Bg3 (23. Rxe2 $4 Qh1#) 23... Rxb2 {White has no time to
save the c4-bishop due to the threat ...Qh1#.}) 21. Kxf2 Ne4+ 22. Kf1 Qf3+ 23.
Kg1 Qf2+ 24. Kh1 Re6 25. Bxd5 Qf3+ 26. Kh2 Rg6 27. Bxf7+ Rxf7 28. Qd8+ Rf8 29.
Qd5+ Kh8 30. Ng3 Qf2+ 0-1

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
