1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 c5 4. exd5 exd5 5. Ngf3 Nc6 6. Bb5 cxd4 7. O-O Bd6 8.
Nb3 Nge7 9. Nfxd4 {The obvious aim of this move is to avoid the pin with ..Bg4.
But it weakens the kingside while generally the chances of a blockade on c5
after Bxc6 are very slim. On top, Black will have no problems playing ...
Ne5-c4.} O-O 10. c3 (10. Re1 a6 (10... Qc7 11. h3 Ne5 {is another possible
move order.}) 11. Bf1 (11. Be2 Qc7 12. h3 Bd7 $11) 11... Ne5 12. c3 Bg4 13. Qc2
(13. f3 Bd7 $11) (13. Be2 Bxe2 14. Rxe2 Nc4 $11) {Agopov,M (2305)-Kokkila,T 
(2285) Tampere 1997 (0-1, 37)} 13... Qc7 14. Bf4 Rae8 15. h3 Bd7 $11 {Black is
perfectly mobilized and has little to fear.}) (10. Bg5 Qc7 {Immediately taking
measures against the plan based on Bh4-g3.} 11. h3 (11. g3 h6 12. Bxe7 Bxe7 13.
c3 a6 14. Bd3 Ne5 15. Bf5 g6 16. Bxc8 Raxc8 17. Nf3 Nc4 18. Rb1 Rfd8 19. Nbd4
Bf6 20. Re1 Kg7 21. Re2 b5 $132 {Lobzhanidze,D (2452)-Zhadanov,N (2230) Moscow
1999 (0-1, 42)}) (11. Qh5 Nf5 12. Bxc6 ({The complications after} 12. Bf6 $5 {
basically lose a pawn:} Ncxd4 13. Nxd4 Nxd4 14. Bxd4 Qxc2 15. Qxd5 Rd8 16. Qh5
Bxh2+ 17. Qxh2 Rxd4 18. Qe5 Qe4) 12... bxc6 13. Bf6 Ne7 14. Bg5 Bd7 15. Rae1
Rae8 $17 {Boehnisch,M (2420)-Uhlmann,W (2570) Goerlitz 1972 (0-1, 55) White
has no way of preventing the central pawns' advance.}) 11... h6 12. Be3 a6 13.
Be2 Rd8 14. c3 Nf5 15. Nxf5 Bxf5 16. Nd4 Be4 17. Bf3 Be5 18. Nxc6 Qxc6 19. Re1
Qb5 {A good example for the effectiveness of piece pressure with the French
Isolani.} 20. Bxe4 dxe4 {with at least equal play for Black, Sax,G (2445)
-Ivkov,B (2520) Hilversum 1973 (1/2-1/2, 67)}) 10... Qc7 11. h3 (11. Qh5 {
exposes the queen with incomplete development.} g6 12. Qh4 Nf5 13. Nxf5 Bxf5
14. Bh6 Rfe8 15. Rfe1 a6 16. Bf1 (16. Qf6 $2 Bxh2+ 17. Kh1 Be5 $19) 16... Be7
17. Bg5 Bd6 $11 18. Rad1 $6 h5 19. f3 Bc2 20. Rxe8+ Rxe8 21. Rxd5 Bxb3 22. axb3
Qb6+ 23. Kh1 Bb8 $15 {threatening ...Ba7.}) 11... Ne5 12. Be2 a6 13. Re1 (13.
Bf4 Bd7) 13... Re8 14. Qc2 N7g6 $11 15. Nf5 $2 {This over optimistic move with
incomplete development leads straight into trouble.} Bxf5 16. Qxf5 Nh4 17. Qh5
(17. Qc2 Nef3+ 18. gxf3 {Magdalinin,A (2202)-Vdovichenko,V Kiev 2005 (0-1, 25)}
Qd7 $19) 17... Nd3 18. Rf1 (18. Rd1 Nxf2 19. Kxf2 Bg3+ 20. Kf1 g6 21. Qxd5 Rad8
$19) 18... g6 19. Qxh4 Rxe2 $17 *

