1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 c5 4. exd5 exd5 5. Ngf3 Nc6 6. Bb5 cxd4 7. Qe2+ $5 {
This is White's only consistent way to avoid a transposition to the classical
main lines.} Qe7 ({Since White has not committed himself to Nxd4,} 7... Be7 $6
{exposes Black to the pin along the e-file:} 8. O-O Nf6 9. Re1 Bd7 10. b3 Kf8
11. Bb2 $14 {Sebag,M (2527)-Vaisser,A (2544) Nancy 2013 (1/2-1/2, 39)}) 8. Ne5
{A premature attempt to punish Black for the chosen move order.} (8. Qxe7+ {
makes Black's play easier, as it helps his development.} Bxe7 9. Nxd4 Bd7 10.
N2f3 Nf6 11. O-O O-O 12. Bd3 {1/2-1/2 Balashov,Y (2490)-Dolmatov,S (2615)
Elista 1995} Rfe8 13. c3 Bc5 14. Be3 Ng4 $5 15. Nxc6 Rxe3 16. fxe3 Bxe3+ 17.
Kh1 bxc6 18. Rae1 Nf2+ 19. Kg1 Nh3+ 20. Kh1 $11) ({For the main continuation} 
8. Nxd4 {see the next lines.}) 8... Bd7 9. Bxc6 {Consistent but double-edged.}
({The simpler} 9. Nxd7 {leads to approximate equality.} Qxe2+ 10. Kxe2 Kxd7 11.
Rd1 a6 12. Ba4 Nf6 13. Nf3 Bc5 14. Nxd4 Bxd4 15. Bxc6+ bxc6 16. Rxd4 Rhe8+ 17.
Kf1 a5 $11) 9... bxc6 10. O-O Kd8 $1 (10... f6 $2 11. Qh5+ g6 12. Nxg6 $16 {
Dolmatov}) 11. Nb3 (11. Re1 f6 12. Nxd7 Qxe2 13. Rxe2 Kxd7 14. Nf3 c5 15. b4
Rb8 16. bxc5 Bxc5 17. Bf4 Rb6 18. Rae1 Nh6 19. Bxh6 gxh6 $15 {White has the
better structure, but his queenside is weak, making his compensation for the
missing pawn questionable.}) 11... f6 12. Bg5 $5 (12. f4 $5 $13 {Anand} Nh6 $5
$15 ({It is safest to delay capturing the knight, but there is no clear
refutation of} 12... fxe5 13. fxe5 Nh6 14. Qa6 Ng4 {either.})) 12... fxg5 13.
Na5 Qe8 $1 {1/2 Ivanchuk,V-Dolmatov,S Manila (izt) 1990.} 14. Rfe1 Kc7 (14...
Bb4 $6 15. Qa6 Bxe1 16. Rxe1 $40 {Dolmatovv}) 15. Qf3 Bb4 (15... Nf6 16. Nexc6
Qh5 17. Qb3 Bxc6 18. Nxc6 Bd6) 16. Qg3 $8 Bd6 17. c4 Nf6 18. Naxc6 $6 (18. c5
$8 Bxe5 19. Rxe5 Nh5 20. Rxe8+ (20. Qxg5 h6 21. Qxh5 Qxh5 22. Rxh5 g5 $19)
20... Nxg3 21. Rxh8 Rxh8 22. hxg3 Rb8 23. Nb3 a5 $17 {Dolmatov}) 18... Ne4 19.
Rxe4 dxe4 20. c5 Bxe5 21. Nxe5 Kc8 $6 22. Nc4 $6 (22. c6 $8 Be6 23. Qa3 a5 $17
{Dolmatov}) 22... Qe7 23. Nd6+ Kd8 $19 24. Qb3 Bc6 25. Qc4 Qf6 {0-1 Svidler,P 
(2585)-Dolmatov,S (2605) Haifa 1995 CBM 046 [Dolmatov]} *

