{[#]After exchanging on c6 in the early middlegame White seems to have
stabilized the position. But Black also has blockading ideas on the kingside.
How did he take over the initiative?} 29... Bxd4 $1 {Eliminating the blocking
knight and weakening White's structure.} 30. cxd4 Qd8 {[%csl Rb4,Rf4] It
suddenly appears that the bishop cannot defend f4 and b4 at the same time.} (
30... Re6 31. Bc5 Qb8 {followed by ...Nf4 is similar}) 31. Bc5 $6 ({It would
have been better to keep the control over f4 with} 31. Bh2 {even though the
king's position looks precarious in view of the back rank threats.} Qe7 32. Qc3
Qe6 $15) 31... Nf4 32. Qf3 Qg5 $17 {With strong kingside initiative, Vogt,
L-Uhlmann,W Potsdam 1974 (0-1, 47)} *

