{[#]Which is the most effective way of dealing with the complex central
tension?} 15... Nxd4 $1 {It appears that all the recaptures have some drawback.
} 16. Bxd4 $6 (16. Nxd4 a6 17. Bf1 Qxb2 $15 {wins a pawn without clear white
compensation.}) (16. cxd4 {may be best, leaving White with the more passive
side of the symmetrical central version.} Bd6 $15) 16... Bxf3 17. Bxc5 (17.
gxf3 Bxd4 18. Qxd4 (18. cxd4 Nf5 $19) 18... Qxb5 19. Rxe7 Qxb2 $17) 17... Qxc5
18. gxf3 {Ivanovic,B-Uhlmann,W (2555) Skopje 1976 (0-1, 63)} d4 $1 {Only this
move, cutting the enemy queen's communication with the weakened kingside and
threatening to weaken the queenside with ...dxc3, too, keeps White's advantage.
} 19. cxd4 ({Black might have overlooked that after} 19. Qxd4 Qxb5 20. Rxe7 {
he wins the rook with} Qg5+) 19... Qg5+ 20. Kh1 Qh4 21. Bf1 Ng6 $15 *

