21... Bxd4 $1 (21... Nd3+ 22. Qxd3 Qxf4+ 23. Qd2 Qxd2+ 24. Kxd2 Rec7 25. Ke2
Bxd4 26. Rxd4 Rxc2+ 27. Rd2 Re8+ 28. Kf3 {offers White surviving chances.}) 22.
Qxd4 (22. Rxd4 Nd3+ $1) 22... Qf5 $1 23. c3 (23. Re2 Nf3 $1 24. gxf3 Rxe2) (23.
Nd3 Nxd3+ 24. Qxd3 Qxd3 25. Rxd3 Rxe1+) (23. Rd2 Nc6) 23... Nc6 {Redirecting
the knight to the winning route with gain of time.} 24. Qd2 Rxe1 25. Rxe1 Nb4
$1 26. g3 ({If} 26. Kd1 {the most convincing is} Nxa2 $1) 26... g5 $1 $19 {
(Variations by Uhlmann) Black not only secures his back rank threatening ...
Rxc3 but also attacks the knight which cannot move due to ...Nd3. Radulov,I 
(2495)-Uhlmann,W (2505) Albena 1983 (0-1, 32)} *

