{[#]White has just occupied the blocking square with his bishop. Due to the
threat on g7 Black has to exchange it either with ...Nxd4 or with ...Bb6.
Which would you choose?} 21... Nxd4 $1 {It is better to keep the bishop as in
this way the knight will be constantly under pressure after ...Bb6. Besides,
the bishop can also contribute to the kingside pressure from its actual
diagonal.} (21... Bb6 22. Bxb6 axb6 23. Nfd4 {allows White to consolidate.}
Nge7 {[%csl Gd5] Defending d5.} 24. a3 Re8 25. Rad1) 22. Nfxd4 Rae8 $5 $15 (
22... Ne7 23. Rae1 Bb6 24. Kg2 Re8 25. Rxe4 dxe4 26. Re1 Nc6 {Velimirovic,D 
(2500)-Uhlmann,W (2515) Vinkovci 1982 (0-1, 49)}) 23. Qxd5 (23. Rad1 Bxf4 24.
gxf4 Nxf4 25. Qf3 Nxh3+ 26. Qxh3 Qg5+ $17) (23. Rf2 Ne7 24. Kg2 Bb6 25. Rd1 g6
$17 26. Qxh6 $2 Nf5 $19) 23... Nxf4 $1 24. gxf4 Qg6+ 25. Kh1 Qg3 *

