{[#]White is under serious pressure and with his last move he has attacked one
of the active knights. Where should it retreat?} 22... Ne5 $1 {Exchanging one
of the knights contributes to the stability of the blockade on d4.} 23. Nxe5 (
23. Qd2 Nxf3+ 24. Nxf3 Ng3 $19) 23... Qxe5 24. Be3 Ng3 $1 (24... Nf4 25. Bxf4
Qxf4 26. Rad1 $6 (26. Nf3 $1 d4 {leads only to a symbolic black advantage.})
26... Bxd4 27. cxd4 Re2 28. g3 Qe4 $15 {with a very promising ending in Stanec,
N (2465)-Eingorn,V (2590) Graz 1997 (0-1, 51)}) 25. Rfe1 (25. Rfd1 Qh5 26. a4
Bxd4 27. Bxd4 Ne2+ 28. Kh1 Nxd4 29. cxd4 Qf5 $15 {with similar play as in the
game.}) (25. fxg3 Rxe3 $19) 25... Bxd4 26. cxd4 Qd6 27. Bd2 (27. fxg3 Qxg3 $17)
