{[#]Even without queens, Black has dynamic minor piece play and attacking
chances against the enemy king. How should he proceed now?} 21... Nd7 $1 {
[%cal Gd7e5,Ge5d3] Black improves the placement of the only piece which was
restricted by the enemy pawns. The knight is heading for e5-d3. Due to the
hanging b2-pawn White cannot regroup with Be2-f1 in time.} 22. Bc2 $2 Bxc2 23.
Rxc2 Bb8 $1 24. Kg3 (24. Bxb8 Ne3+) 24... Bxf4+ 25. Kxf4 Rh3 $1 {Black has a
decisive mating attack now.} 26. Rf2 Nde5 27. Rd1 Ng6+ 28. Kg5 Rh6 29. Re2 {
0-1 Donchev,D (2520)-Eingorn,V (2590) Debrecen 1992} f6+ 30. Kf5 Nd6# *

