{[#]I hope you will find it inspiring to play the whole final attacking
sequence move by move.} 19... Rae8 {[%cal Ga7d4] Threatening to win a piece
with ...Bxd4.} 20. f3 Re3 21. Qd2 Bd7 22. Kf2 Bb8 {[%cal Gh6g5] Planning ...
Qg5, with a decisive weakening of the dark squares.} 23. f4 Rxg3 $1 {The
clearest win.} 24. Kxg3 g5 (24... Re4 25. Rf1 g5 {also wins.}) (24... Bxf4+ {
also wins after} 25. Qxf4 g5 {and the queen does not have good squares to
prevent ...Qh4.}) 25. Kf2 Bxf4 26. Nf5 Bxf5 27. Bd3 Qh4+ 28. Kf1 Qh1+ 29. Kf2
Rxe1 30. Qxe1 Bg3+ {0-1 Kovalev,A-Eingorn,V (2450) Soviet Union 1983} 31. Kxg3
Qh4+ 32. Kf3 Qf4+ 33. Ke2 Bg4# *

