{[#]Black to move. Is the impression that White has the initiative true?} 14...
Qb6 $1 {[%csl Gb7][%cal Rb6b2,Rd5d4] This move defends b7, attacks b2 and
prepares ...d5-d4. It appears that the d6-knight is White's main hope for...
maintaining the equality.} 15. Qb3 d4 16. cxd4 Nxd4 17. Nxd4 Qxd4 18. Qc4 Nd5 {
A typical Uhlmann intermediate move.} 19. Bg3 Qxb2 20. Bf3 Nc3 $15 {This
knight's local domination is more effective than that of its rival.} 21. a4 Bb1
$1 {This is even stronger than the game continuation.} (21... Rad8 22. Rfe1 h5
23. h4 b6 $17 {Nijboer,F (2485)-Uhlmann,W (2505) Amsterdam 1990 (0-1, 49)}) 22.
Ne4 {Attacking f6. Otherwise White would lose an exchange without compensation.
} Bxe4 23. Bxe4 Rfd8 {Black has kept his active knight while White did not.
Besides, Black is also a pawn up.} 24. Bf3 Rac8 25. Qg4 Rc5 $17 *

