{[#]White has a firm blockade on d4 but Black has an obvious idea to turn
things dynamic. Should he execute it at once or preparing it with one more
move?} 17... Qd7 $1 ({Slightly more promising than} 17... Nb4 18. Bh7+ Kh8 19.
Qb1 Qd7 (19... Ng6 20. Qf5 $14) 20. cxb4 Ng6 21. g4 Bxg4 22. Bxg6 fxg6 23. Qxg6
Bxh3 $13) 18. Kg2 Nb4 19. Bh7+ $6 (19. Qb1 $2 {turns the black light-squared
bishop into a terrible force.} Nxd3 20. Qxd3 Bg6 21. Qd2 Be4 22. Kh2 Ng6 $17 {
/\...f5}) ({The main merit of Vaganian's queen move consists of the fact that
White had to deviate frorm the line given above with} 19. Bf5 $5 {ensuring
