{[#]Black has some problems to defend his Isolani as the h4-bishop exerts very
nasty pressure. Which is the best way to get rid of any troubles?} 29... Nc6 $1
{Defending the pawn indirectly and preparing the next move.} 30. Kg2 (30. Qxd5
$2 Qxd5 31. Rxd5 Nb4 $17) 30... d4 $1 {[%cal Ga5d5] The thematic pawn break,
clearing the d5-square for the queen.} 31. cxd4 (31. Nxd4 Nxd4 32. cxd4 Qd5+
33. f3 Qxd4 $11) 31... Qd5 32. Qg5 $6 Ne5 $1 {[%cal Rd5g2,Rd5d1] Using the
double pin and the hanging position of the c2-rook.} (32... Qe4 33. Rcd2 $11 {
Kholmov,R (2540)-Uhlmann,W (2575) Halle/Saale 1978 (0-1, 40)}) 33. Qxe5 (33.
dxe5 Qxd1 $17) 33... Qxe5 34. Rxc8 Qb5 35. Rxe8+ Qxe8 36. d5 f6 37. d6 Qd7 $15
*

