{[#]With the knight placed on a reasonable square, White would have drawing
chances due to the blockade on the light squares. But the way it is, Black has
a convincing way to victory.} 33... Qa4+ 34. Kb1 d3 $1 {The dynamic force of
the Isolani can be felt even in positions with few pieces.} 35. g4 Qxc2+ 36.
Qxc2 dxc2+ 37. Kxc2 Be5 {White is practically playing with a piece down.} 38.
b3 (38. Ng3 Bxg3 39. fxg3 f5 $19) 38... f5 39. f3 fxg4 40. fxg4 b5 41. Kd3 Kf7
42. Ke3 Ke7 43. Kd3 Kd6 {0-1 Kupreichik,V (2575)-Vaganian,R (2565) Erevan 
(Armenia) 1981} *

