{[#]Black is slightly better developed and has all pieces optimally placed.
Which is the best way to retain a small plus?} 22... Re4 $1 $15 {[%cal Re4a4,
Gd5d4] Apart from the general knowledge about pieces sustained by the Isolani,
this move is irritating for White because it attacks a4 and may prepare ...
d5-d4 in some cases.} 23. Rd1 $6 ({White should probably adopt a half-waiting
policy with} 23. g3 h5 24. h4 Nd8 $5 {[%cal Gd8e6,Ye4g4] planning ...Ne6 and
if given the necessity, ...Rg4, with some light pressure.}) (23. Nbd2 Re2 24.
Rf1 d4 $15) (23. Qd1 d4 24. cxd4 Nxd4 25. Nbxd4 Bxd4 26. Nxd4 Rxd4 27. Qc2 Qb4
$15 {White should be able to reach a rook ending with a pawn down which is
basically drawn, but this would still mean struggling for a long time.}) 23...
Rxa4 24. Rxd5 Ra2 25. Rd2 a4 26. Nc1 Ra1 $17 {O'Donnell,T (2410)-Vaganian,R 
(2605) Toronto 1990 (0-1, 85)} *

