{[#]White has sacrificed a bishop on h6 to get a very dangerous attack. Is
there a way that Black can stay in the game?} 15... Qb6 $1 {The only good move,
providing some indirect defence along the 6th rank and removing the queen from
an exposed square.} (15... Bc8 $2 16. Qxh6 f5 ({One of the points behind ...
Qb6 can be seen after} 16... Bf5 17. Rxe7 $1) 17. Qg5+ $1 (17. Ng5 Nc6 $14 {
Sigurjonsson,G-Uhlmann,W Raach 1969 (0-1, 34)}) 17... Kf7 18. Qh5+ Kg8 (18...
Kg7 19. Ng5) 19. c4 $3 {A very strong move, preparing the bishop's inclusion
into the attack.} d4 (19... Rf6 20. cxd5) (19... dxc4 20. Ng5 Nc6 21. Bxc4+)
20. Ng5 Nc6 21. c5 $18) ({Other queen moves are weaker than ...Qb6.} 15... Qd8
16. Nd4 $16) (15... Qc8 16. Qxh6 Bf5 17. Qxd6 $18) 16. Qxh6 (16. Re2 Bc5 $17 {
followed by ...Bf5.}) 16... Bf5 17. Qg5+ Bg6 18. h4 Bc5 19. Rxe7 Bxe7 20. Qxe7
Qxb2 {White has good compensation for the exchange but not more.} *

